# Supabase Rules

## General
- Supabase client is accessed via `supabase.instance.client` — never instantiate a new client
- All Supabase calls live in `lib/data/repositories/` — zero exceptions
- Always `await` Supabase calls — never fire and forget

## Queries
- Always filter by `is_active = true` when querying `phrases`
- Always scope user queries with `user_id = auth.uid()` — never fetch all users' data
- Use `.upsert()` with `onConflict` for `user_progress` (unique on `user_id, phrase_id`)
- Use `Future.wait([])` for parallel writes — never await in a loop

## Auth
- Guest login: `supabase.auth.signInAnonymously()`
- Google login: `supabase.auth.signInWithOAuth(OAuthProvider.google)`
- On sign out: call `cacheService.clearAll()` before signing out
- Check `supabase.auth.currentUser` for auth state — never cache auth state manually
- Create profile row immediately after first sign-in if it doesn't exist

## Storage
- Bucket: `phrase-images` (public)
- Image URL format: `https://[project].supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/phrase-images/[phrase_id].png`
- Optional CDN resize (Pro / dashboard-enabled transforms): `.env` `SUPABASE_IMAGE_TRANSFORMS=true` — handled in `supabase_storage_image_url.dart`; default off so object URLs keep working on free tier
- Never upload images at runtime — all images are pre-uploaded by the dev team

## Error Handling
- Catch `PostgrestException` separately from general exceptions
- On Supabase failure: return cached data if available, throw readable exception if not
- Never expose raw Supabase error messages to the UI — map to Urdu user-facing messages
